CBT corn futures traded firmer early,holding gains of 1-1/4 cents to 3/4 cent per bushel inmoderately light early trade.    Yesterday's sharp jump in the weekly corn export figure toabout three times last year's weekly inspections, plus theoutlook for a continued active export pace due to the declinein the U.S. dollar this year, supported nearbys, traders said.    Cargill, the Illinois Co-op, Refco and ADM were thefeatured buyers of old crop May, with CIS a buyer in new cropDecember, pit brokers said. Reuter&#3;